./confluent local stop
./confluent local start
./confluent local destroy
./confluent local start kafka

Multiple kafka:
---------------

1) 
cd config -> 
cp server.properties server0.properties
cp server.properties server1.properties
cp server.properties server2.properties

2) Change below properties
change brolker.id =1
log.dirs  = ......./kafka1
listeners = PLAINTTEXT ... 9093

3) Create log dirs:
../
mkdir data/kafka1
nkdir data/kafka2

4) start in diff terminal
zookeeper-server-start config/zookeeper.properties

5) start in diff terminal
kafka-server-start config/server0.properties
kafka-server-start config/server1.properties

Kafka on docker:
----------------
https://github.com/conduktor/kafka-stack-docker-compose



Problems:
----------
> The topics list is disappearing
Make sure you have changed the Zookeeper dataDir=/path/to/data/zookeeper , and Kafka log.dirs=/path/to/data/kafka



Kafka in windows:
-----------------

run from :/bin/windows/kafka-...bat
same as path:
setting up path: 

goto environment -> Env variables -> Edit path variable -> New -> Paste absolute path
c:\\kakfa\bin\windows

You can now type kafka commands from any directory: kafka.bat
Use all bat files instead of .sh files.




Kafka in Linux:
----------------
1) sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk
2) same as map:
3) Update kafka path for the command:
.bachrc

export PATH = /home/name/kafka../bin:$PATH





Kafka in MAC: [Java and kafka binaries are required]
-----------------
1) Download jar  or brew install kafka
2) tar -xvf kafka.tar.gz 
3) cd /bin/kakfa_topics.sh

brew tap caskroom/versions
brew cask install java8

4) cat ~/.bash_profile
5) cd bin
6) pwd
7) Get the path and nano ~/.bash_profile
8) export PATH="$PATH:/Users/stephanemaarek/kafka../bin"
9) Open new tab and then kafka-  + type tab and then you will see all kafka command.

Open a terminal window:
zookeeper-server-start config/zookeeper.properties
in zookeeper.properties => Change the data directory

Open another terminal window: for brokers
kakfa-server-start config/server.properties
in server.properties =>log.dirs=.../kafka





